ettings.</p></section><section><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">10. Limitation of Liability</h3><p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">PageGains is provided “as is” without any warranty of any kind. To the fullest extent permitted by law, J2FB SAS shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages — including loss of profits, revenue, or business — arising from your use of or inability to use the service, even if we have been advised of the possibility of such damages. Our total liability to you for any claim arising from these terms shall not exceed the amount you paid us in the twelve months preceding the claim.</p></section><section><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">11. Governing Law</h3><p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">These Terms of Service are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of France. Any disputes arising out of or relating to these terms or your use of PageGains shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Paris, France.</p></section><section><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">12. Changes to Terms</h3><p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. We will notify you of material changes by email or by displaying a notice in the service. Your continued use of PageGains after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated terms.</p></section><section><h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">13. Indemnification</h3><p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless J2FB SAS and its officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any claims, damages, obligations, losses, liabilities, costs, or expenses (including attorneys&#x27; fees) arising from: (a) your use of the service; (b) your violation of these Terms of Service; or (c) your violation of any third-party rights.</p></section><section><h3 class="t